      • setOutputPartitionKey

        public static void setOutputPartitionKey(Map<String,String> arguments,
                         PartitionKey key)
        Set the partition key of the output partition when using PartitionedFileSet as an OutputFormatProvider. This key is used as the partition key for the new file, and also to generate an output file path - if that path is not explicitly given as an argument itself.
        Parameters:
        key - the partition key
        arguments - the runtime arguments for a partitioned dataset

        Parameters:

        Returns:

      • addInputPartitions

        public static void addInputPartitions(Map<String,String> arguments,
                      Iterator<? extends Partition> partitionIterator)
        Sets partitions as input for a PartitionedFileSet. If both a PartitionFilter and Partition(s) are specified, the PartitionFilter takes precedence and the specified Partition(s) will be ignored.
        Parameters:
        arguments - the runtime arguments for a partitioned dataset
        partitionIterator - the iterator of partitions to add as input

      • addInputPartitions

        public static void addInputPartitions(Map<String,String> arguments,
                      Iterable<? extends Partition> partitions)
        Sets partitions as input for a PartitionedFileSet. If both a PartitionFilter and Partition(s) are specified, the PartitionFilter takes precedence and the specified Partition(s) will be ignored.
        Parameters:
        arguments - the runtime arguments for a partitioned dataset
        partitions - an iterable of partitions to add as input
